Reasoning: The paper analyzes user dwell time on news pages in a smartphone application, which involves user behavior and interaction with technology. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with search engines and recommender systems, or the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with user interfaces and user experience. The paper also mentions the use of categories for news pages, which could fall under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category, which deals with natural language processing and text classification. Additionally, the paper analyzes the correlation between dwell time and length of news page, which could involve the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category, which deals with control and communication in systems, or the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, which deals with network analysis and information diffusion.
